                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.512351 Double/259: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-12T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 12, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 12—7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>585. Reference my despatch No. 1769 of April 9, 1935. Department will recall that
                    article 2 of law of April 5 approving double taxation convention provides that
                    decree of ratification may in accordance with understanding with American
                    authorities put convention into force at earlier date than January 1, 1936.</p>
                <p>A note has just been received from the Foreign Office suggesting that in
                    accordance with the above provision an earlier date be fixed and asking the
                    American Government to propose the date which seems most appropriate to it.</p>
                <p>Telegraphic instructions would be appreciated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
